I"|<h1 id="pontifications">Pontifications</h1>

<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">jekyll serve</code> broke my RSS feed (which <a href="https://www.zylstra.org/blog/2019/09/9069/">Ton discovered,</a> thanks)</li>
  <li>The solution is to use the ruby bundler in production mode (after setting jekyll up with the ruby bundler as per the official docs: <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/tutorials/using-jekyll-with-bundler/">Using Jekyll with Bundler</a>):
    <ul>
      <li>namely <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">JEKYLL_ENV=production bundle exec jekyll serve</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
